<StackPanel
    x:Class="UnitedSets.UI.Controls.HomeBackground"
    xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
    VerticalAlignment="Center"
    Grid.Row="1"
    HorizontalAlignment="Center"
    Canvas.ZIndex="-1"
>
    <StackPanel Orientation="Horizontal" HorizontalAlignment="Center">
        <!--<Image x:Name="AppFontIcon"
                HorizontalAlignment="Left" 
                VerticalAlignment="Center"
                Source="Assets\Square150x150Logo.scale-100.png"   
                Width="48" 
                Height="48"/>-->
        <TextBlock
                Text="United Sets"
                VerticalAlignment="Center"
                
                FontSize="28"/> <!--Margin="8, 0, 0, 0"-->
        <TextBlock
                Text="- Preview Beta"
                VerticalAlignment="Center"
                Margin="8, 0, 0, 0"
                Opacity="0.7"
                FontSize="24"/>
    </StackPanel>
    <TextBlock FontSize="14" FontWeight="SemiBold" Margin="0, 0, 0, 4">Tips:</TextBlock>
    <TextBlock>
            • Hold SHIFT while clicking + icon to create Splitable Tab<LineBreak/>
            • Drag a Tab out to release the Window<LineBreak/>
            • Hold CTRL while dragging other window into United Sets to add the window<LineBreak/>
            • Hold SHIFT while opening new United Sets window to separate taskbar icons<LineBreak/>
            • [Experimental] Hold ALT while adding window to make it borderless<LineBreak/>
            • [Experimental] Double Click On Tab to open window settings
    </TextBlock>
    <TextBlock FontSize="14" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#e96e60" Margin="0, 12, 0, 4">Preview Warnings:</TextBlock>
    <TextBlock>
        • UWP applications are not stable yet<LineBreak/>
        • [Experimental] Save and Close may sometimes fail to add<LineBreak/>
        windows back to United Sets.<LineBreak/>
        • [Experimental] Save and Close will NOT work for system<LineBreak/>
        UWP/Packaged apps such as Calculator/Paint/Notepad/etc.<LineBreak/>
        (It will still work for user installed ones)<LineBreak/>
        and will not work for one-process-only app (such as File Explorer)<LineBreak/>
        such as (Calculator/Paint/Notepad/etc.).<LineBreak/>
        • [Experimental] Removing title bar makes some app undragable,<LineBreak/>
        therefore, it is advised not to do that for windows in Splitable Tab.<LineBreak/>
    </TextBlock>
</StackPanel>
